
[1]restlessness

   REST'LESSNESS, n.

   1. Uneasiness; unquietness; a state of disturbance or agitation, either
   of body or mind.

   2. Want of sleep or rest; uneasiness.

   3. Motion; agitation; as the restlessness of the magnetic needle.
